NORMAL AND TEMPERED
FINGER-POSITION.

In order to distinguish with

greater precision the difference in

_- intonation of intervals relative to an

‚Äú -- _ypper or a lower open string, we

‚Äî~ \shall designate the tones formed

with a lower open string as ‚ÄúNormal

Tones‚Äù; those formed with an

upper ‚Äòopen string as ‚ÄúTempered

Tones‚Äù (Normal and. Tempered
‚ÄòFinger-Position).

In the tempered finger-position
the distance of the first finger and
thumb from the nut is about 14 of
an inch greater than in the normal
position:

